Package com.intellij.util.containers

Class ConcurrentFactoryMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.util.containers.ConcurrentFactoryMap<K,V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentMap<K,V>, java.util.Map<K,V>

    public abstract class ConcurrentFactoryMap<K,V>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentMap<K,V>
    ConcurrentMap which computes the value associated with the key (via create(Object) method) on first get(Object) access. This map is THREAD SAFE. It's guaranteed that two get(Object) method calls with the same key will return the same value (i.e. the created value stored atomically). For the not thread-safe (but possibly faster and more memory-efficient) alternative please use FactoryMap instead.
